This is an original automation script for installing OS packages online and in
air-gapped environments. It uses the host distribution's package toolchains (all
credit to their respective authors / distributions):

  apt / dpkg-dev          (Debian/Ubuntu)
  dnf / dnf-utils / createrepo_c   (RHEL family)
  zypper                  (SLES / openSUSE)

When the `save` mode builds an offline package repository, it redistributes
operating-system distribution packages. **Each such package retains its own
upstream license** — this project does not relicense them; it only repackages
them for offline installation. Consult your distribution for the licenses of the
specific packages you bundle.
